   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TEN IN THE BUILDING UP OF THE CHURCH Scripture Reading: Matt 16:18; Eph 4:11-12, 15-16; Col 2:19; 1 Cor 12:28, 18; Rom 12:3; 1 Cor 12:24, 6; 14:25 OUTLINE In Christ: Christ will build up His church Matt 16:18.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>He gave some apostles, some prophets, some evangelists, and some shepherds and teachers for the perfecting of the saints unto the building up of the Body of Christ Eph 4:11-12.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>His believers grow up in all things into Him, the Head; out from Him all the Body grows unto the building up of itself Eph 4:15-16.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>By God: Out from the Head all the Body grows with the growth of God Col 2:19.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God has placed in the church, first apostles, second prophets, third teachers; then works of power, then gifts of healing, helps, administrations, various kinds of tongues 1 Cor 12:28.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>God has placed the members, each one of them, in the Body, even as He willed 1 Cor 12:18.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>God has apportioned to each a measure of faith Rom 12:3.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>God has blended the Body together 1 Cor 12:24.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The same God operates all things in all 1 Cor 12:6.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>God is among you the church 1 Cor 14:25.</S>
   </TEXT>
